http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/SC-asks-discoms-why-they-cannot-be-audited-by-CAG/article14005603.ece

: The Supreme Court on Monday asked three private power distribution companies to explain why they cannot be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.A Bench led by Justice J. Chelameswar posed the query on several appeals, including those filed by the Delhi government, the CAG and the United RWAs Joint Action, challenging a decision by the Delhi High Court that they are outside the purview of a CAG audit as they come under the jurisdiction of the Delhi Electricity Regulatory Commission (DERC).The Bench directed Tata Power Delhi Distribution Ltd (TPDDL), BSES Rajdhani Power Ltd. and BSES Yamuna Power Ltd. to respond in four weeks. The case has been posted for hearing on March 2.In its verdict, the Delhi High Court had quashed the AAP government’s January 7, 2014, directive for a CAG audit of the discoms supplying power in Delhi on grounds including that it owns 49 per cent stake in them.The High Court, in its October 30, 2015, order had termed the AAP government’s decision “populist”. The discoms are a 51:49 per cent joint venture between the private companies and the Delhi government.The Delhi High Court had quashed the AAP’s directive for a CAG auditof the discoms